Specimen information

Test19-DEC-2019Specimen
Appearance of UrineCloudy urineUrine
Odor of UrineUrine smell ammoniacalUrine
Clarity of UrineTranslucentUrine
Color of UrineBrown colorUrine

Annotation

Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
Renal function is impaired as indicated by elevated serum creatinine. Urinalysis shows proteinuria, glucosuria, low specific gravity, and abnormal urine appearance (cloudy, brown, ammoniacal), suggesting possible renal tubular dysfunction or chronic kidney disease. No evidence of urinary tract infection (negative nitrites, leukocytes, hemoglobin). Recommend further nephrological evaluation and monitoring of renal function.
